-- Fed Appoints Jon Faust as Special Adviser to Board on Policy
-- B y   J a m e s   T y s o n
-- 2012-01-13T15:00:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-30/fed-policy-makers-sharpen-differences-over-bond-purchase-policy.html
The Federal Reserve Board announced
today the appointment of Jon Faust as a special adviser on
monetary policy and international issues.  Faust, an economics professor at  Johns Hopkins University 
in Baltimore, will focus on monetary policy and contribute to
the Federal Open Market Committee’s subcommittee on
communications, the Fed said today in a statement in  Washington .  He will also work with the Division of International
Finance, the Fed said. The appointment is effective Jan. 17,
according to the Fed.  Prior to joining the Johns Hopkins faculty in 2006, Faust
served as assistant director in the Fed’s division of
International Finance, the central bank said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
James Tyson in Washington at 
